INSERT INTO `field_data_body` VALUES ('node','custom_page','0','14','14','und','0','<h2>Where can I get some?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>There are many variations of passages of Lorem Ipsum available, but the majority have suffered alteration in some form, by injected humour, or randomised words which don''t look even slightly believable. If you are going to use a passage of Lorem Ipsum, you need to be sure there isn''t anything embarrassing hidden in the middle of text. All the Lorem Ipsum generators on the Internet tend to repeat predefined chunks as necessary, making this the first true generator on the Internet. It uses a dictionary of over 200 Latin words, combined with a handful of model sentence structures, to generate Lorem Ipsum which looks reasonable. The generated Lorem Ipsum is therefore always free from repetition, injected humour, or non-characteristic words etc.</p>\r\n','','full_html'),('node','custom_page','0','15','15','und','0','<h2>Where does it&nbsp;from?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Contrary to popular belief, Lorem Ipsum is not simply random text. It has roots in a piece of classical Latin literature from 45 BC, making it over 2000 years old. Richard McClintock, a Latin professor at Hampden-Sydney College in Virginia, looked up one of the more obscure Latin words, consectetur, from a Lorem Ipsum passage, and going through the cites of the word in classical literature, discovered the undoubtable source. Lorem Ipsum comes from sections 1.10.32 and 1.10.33 of "de Finibus Bonorum et Malorum" (The Extremes of Good and Evil) by Cicero, written in 45 BC. This book is a treatise on the theory of ethics, very popular during the Renaissance. The first line of Lorem Ipsum, "Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet..", comes from a line in section 1.10.32.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The standard chunk of Lorem Ipsum used since the 1500s is reproduced below for those interested. Sections 1.10.32 and 1.10.33 from "de Finibus Bonorum et Malorum" by Cicero are also reproduced in their exact original form, accompanied by English versions from the 1914 translation by H. Rackham.</p>\r\n','','full_html');
INSERT INTO `field_data_body` VALUES ('node','custom_page','0','16','16','und','0','<h2>Why do we use it?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>It is a long established fact that a reader will be distracted by the readable content of a page when looking at its layout. The point of using Lorem Ipsum is that it has a more-or-less normal distribution of letters, as opposed to using ''Content here, content here'', making it look like readable English. Many desktop publishing packages and web page editors now use Lorem Ipsum as their default model text, and a search for ''lorem ipsum'' will uncover many web sites still in their infancy. Various versions have evolved over the years, sometimes by accident, sometimes on purpose (injected humour and the like).</p>\r\n','','full_html'),('node','custom_page','0','17','17','und','0','<h2>What is Lorem Ipsum?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Lorem Ipsum</strong>&nbsp;is simply dummy text of the printing and typesetting industry. Lorem Ipsum has been the industry''s standard dummy text ever since the 1500s, when an unknown printer took a galley of type and scrambled it to make a type specimen book. It has survived not only five centuries, but also the leap into electronic typesetting, remaining essentially unchanged. It was popularised in the 1960s with the release of Letraset sheets containing Lorem Ipsum passages, and more recently with desktop publishing software like Aldus PageMaker including versions of Lorem Ipsum</p>\r\n','','full_html'),('node','custom_article','0','36','36','und','0','<p>One of Australia’s leading property figures is quietly confident the market’s post-winter resurgence will be maintained.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Auction numbers and clearance rates in our biggest cities continue to strengthen as the sharp downturn of the past two years begins to show more positive signs of a prolonged uplift.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Led by the booming prestige market in Sydney, clearance rates in the Harbour City averaged an incredible 85 per cent for September, just ahead of Melbourne’s rate of 79 per cent.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="news1.jpeg" height="450" src="/assignment2/drupal/sites/default/files/news1.jpeg" width="800" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Those figures were well up on this time last year: 51 per cent and 56 per cent respectively.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>According to First National Real Estate CEO Ray Ellis, there are several vital signals pointing to improved market conditions.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Confidence in the market is back</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>“What you’re seeing is confidence coming back,” Mr Ellis said.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>“We had a property in Sydney just recently that went for $250,000 over the reserve and there were 10 bidders there. In the main, the average Australian has confidence in the market again.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>“I’m not talking across the board but it is happening.”</p>\r\n\r\n<p>As the below graphs illustrates, Brisbane and Canberra are in tune with the strengthening markets in Sydney and Melbourne, while Adelaide and Perth don’t have the same momentum and Hobart has fallen well behind.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="news3.jpeg" height="230" src="/assignment2/drupal/sites/default/files/news3.jpeg" width="410" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="news4.jpeg" height="226" src="/assignment2/drupal/sites/default/files/news4.jpeg" width="401" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Pent up demand is exploding</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Australians who have waited around two or three years to move home, due to concerns about what is happening in the market, are viewing now as the time to strike.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>“Pent-up demand is fuelling the market,” Mr Ellis said.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="news5.jpeg" height="450" src="/assignment2/drupal/sites/default/files/news5.jpeg" width="800" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>They could sit on their hands before. Market factors were creating confusion. There was the (federal) election, the royal commission. Those factors are gone and interest rates are at a record low. And buyers know the rates are going to stay that low for two or three years.”</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Investors are coming back</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The below graph sourced from property data firm&nbsp;<a href="https://www.hometrack.com.au/" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">Hometrack</a>, illustrates why owner/occupiers and investors were scared off by the depth of the recent downturn in the property market.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="news6.jpeg" height="214" src="/assignment2/drupal/sites/default/files/news6.jpeg" width="500" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>But the change in those market conditions, has drawn investors back in alongside owner/occupiers.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>“Investors are returning to the market, they too see opportunity,” Mr Ellis said.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>“Savvy investors are returning to selected areas such as the Tweed Valley and Coffs Harbour. In Hobart yields are up. In the Southern Highlands yields are up.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>“You only have to look at the latest ABS stats to see that investment confidence is returning.”</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Australia Bureau of Statistics data from August on&nbsp;<a href="https://www.abs.gov.au/ausstats/abs@.nsf/mf/5601.0" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">Lending on households and businesses</a>, recording lending commitments to households rising by 3.2 per cent in August, after a 4.3 per cent rise in July.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>“Most sales are a family home decision. It’s emotional. It’s not an investment decision. It’s empty nesters, downsizers, upsizers making their move. They can leave that move for two to three years, before they enter the market. That is what we are now seeing.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><iframe frameborder="0" height="315" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/9Npt8VRBOhk" width="560"></iframe></p>\r\n\r\n<p>According to the ABS, “The rise in lending to households was driven by refinancing of household loans (up 7.7 per cent), followed by investment dwellings excluding refinancing (up 5.7 per cent) and owner occupier dwellings excluding refinancing (up 1.9 per cent).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>“All in all, it’s producing a good market environment,” Mr Ellis said.</p>\r\n','','full_html');
INSERT INTO `field_data_body` VALUES ('node','product','0','37','37','und','0','<p>KINGSCLIFF''S PREMIER BEACHFRONT HOME - THIS PRIVATE RESIDENCE TRULY IS THE JEWEL IN THE TWEED COAST CROWN ...<br />\r\n	Spanning just under two thousand square metres "NORTH POINT RESIDENCE" is one of the most luxurious properties in northern NSW.<br />\r\n	Designed by award-winning architect, Paul Uhlmann, this five-bedroom home offers exclusive beach access, an eighteen metre resort-style saltwater swimming pool, and a full-sized flood-lit tennis court.<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	Whitewashed, wide oak floorboards, high ceilings, polished concrete flooring and custom stonework are all features that emphasise the use of natural elements to reflect our coastal surrounds.<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	Life here is luxurious, yet practical and comfortable, with fully ducted heating and cooling, eco smart indoor fireplaces and extensive wrap-around decking that invites the beautifully landscaped outdoors, in.<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	The parent''s retreat is known as the "Round House" &amp; is connected to the main house, but designed for complete privacy &amp; as a separate adult relaxation zone.<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	The lower level incorporates a lounge room with fireplace, overlooking the manicured gardens and swimming pool. There is a powder room to service the tennis court and swimming pool guests and a home office or gymnasium area.<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	The top floor master suite is a true seaside sanctuary, where you can:<br />\r\n	- open curtains to your elevated view with the touch of a button<br />\r\n	- browse an expansive walk through wardrobe<br />\r\n	- and delight in a lavish ensuite complete with his &amp; hers Calcutta marble benchtops and deluxe tapware.<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	The stunning open plan lounge, dining and kitchen area is orientated to the north allowing abundant light, winter sunshine and cooling summer breezes into the home.<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	Central to the home is the designer kitchen which makes meal preparation a breeze &amp; is generous in size, where family and friends can gather with ease. It boasts stone benchtops, custom cabinetry, a built-in Miele coffee machine, zip tap with hot/cold &amp; sparkling water, double ovens, European appliances &amp; loads of storage.<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	"NORTH POINT RESIDENCE" WILL AWAKEN YOUR SENSES &amp; WILL IMPRESS THE MOST DISCERNING BUYER !!!<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	PROPERTY FEATURES:<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	- 5 BEDROOMS (2 with ensuites)<br />\r\n	- 3 BATHROOMS<br />\r\n	- 2 POWDER ROOMS<br />\r\n	- OFFICE/STUDY/HOME GYM<br />\r\n	- 2 GENEROUS LIVING AREAS<br />\r\n	- FULL SIZED FLOOD LIT TENNIS COURT<br />\r\n	- 18M RESORT STYLE SALTWATER POOL WITH DUAL FILTRATION SYSTEM AND OVERFLOW PLUS AUTOMATIC TOP UP<br />\r\n	- 2 CAR GARAGE WITH STORAGE<br />\r\n	- VIDEO INTERCOM<br />\r\n	- EXTENSIVE USE OF FEATURE STONE THROUGHOUT<br />\r\n	- IN GROUND IRRIGATION SYSTEM<br />\r\n	- SPRAWLING LANDSCAPED GROUNDS WITH MATURE TREES, FEATURE PLANTS &amp; EXTENSIVE LIGHTING<br />\r\n	- FULLY DUCTED HEATING AND COOLING<br />\r\n	- TWO ECO SMART INDOOR FIREPLACES<br />\r\n	- 100SQM WRAP AROUND DECKING<br />\r\n	- DIRECT BEACH ACCESS<br />\r\n	- 1959 SQM BEACHFRONT LAND PARCEL<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	CONTACT NICK WITHERIFF on 0405 618 477 or CAROL WITHERIFF on 0413 056 405 FOR YOUR PRIVATE VIEWING OF "NORTH POINT RESIDENCE".<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	15 MINUTES TO GOLD COAST AIRPORT<br />\r\n	30 MINUTES TO BYRON BAY<br />\r\n	CLOSE TO SALT VILLAGE, CAFES, SHOPS, RESTAURANTS, SALT SURF CLUB, SCHOOLS, CHILD-CARE, MEDICAL, BUS-STOP, COLES SHOPPING CENTRE &amp; KINGSCLIFF TOWNSHIP.</p>\r\n','','full_html');
INSERT INTO `field_data_body` VALUES ('node','product','0','38','38','und','0','<p>A Paul Clout masterpiece in an esteemed dress circle where timeless design meets resort style living. Facing north to water, the expansive home''s unique layout ensures streaming light, tailored breezes and water views throughout.<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	| Palatial resort style Clout designed home<br />\r\n	| North west aspect with a long water view<br />\r\n	| 20 meters of direct water frontage<br />\r\n	| Private jetty for boat mooring and access to the Noosa River<br />\r\n	| Infinity pool in with northern position.<br />\r\n	| Central courtyard, multiple outdoor living zones<br />\r\n	| Air-conditioning<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	Created in a pavilion style, there is a distinction between the rooms however a natural flow that ensures they don''t feel segregated from one-another. Designed to embrace the northern aspect, the house wraps around a central courtyard separating it into two distinct halves, joined by a curved walkway which peels off upstairs. Bi-fold doors stretch the length of the home opening to the alfresco &amp; wet edge pool on the waterfront.<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	A palatial master suite keeps an eye over the water to the sunset each night as does the bath in the tile lined ensuite. Each subsequent room includes an ensuite &amp; built-in robe creating substantial guest accommodation.<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	Benefit from a lifestyle like no other with direct water frontage to a private canal. A timber jetty gives access and mooring to your boat while it''s just a short ride to the lock and main Noosa River.</p>\r\n','','full_html'),('node','product','0','39','39','und','0','<p>Nestled well back from the road in an elevated setting, this stylish residence would be right at home on the Almalfi Coast; lucky for you, the spectacular views span Pittwater, as far as the eye can see. Designed to take full advantage of a sun-drenched position, the home is one of graceful lines and exquisite proportion; gently curved architraves, high beamed ceilings, French doors and casement windows add tremendous character and warmth, while expansive terraces extend from both levels, connecting to lush lawns and a saltwater pool.<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	- Double brick construction; warm in winter and cool in summer months<br />\r\n	- Free-flowing living spaces with dual lounges and defined dining area<br />\r\n	- Fabulous entertaining options with expansive terrace, outdoor kitchen<br />\r\n	- Sun-drenched deck &amp; saltwater pool; Smeg kitchen w/timber benchtops<br />\r\n	- Wonderful Pittwater views from master suite; all bedrooms with BIRs<br />\r\n	- Guest w/c, timber/tile floors, garage + three offstreet parking spots<br />\r\n	- Superb fulltime residence, great weekender; steps from the foreshore</p>\r\n','','full_html');
INSERT INTO `field_data_body` VALUES ('node','agent','0','40','40','und','0','<h2>About&nbsp;Steven Khawam</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Dedicated to engage in real-estate practices, Steven is well respected by all communities he serves.<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	Having the knowledge and experience in residential, commercial as well as a large variety of high rise to standard developments, Steven will assure and lead sellers and buyers to the right path and accuracy in information he provides.<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	He is excellent for working with the people and community he serves for and does his very best in and assures in the most comfortable and easy process in real-estate.<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	Recently, he achieved ranking within the top sales people in the entire LJ Hooker worldwide network of 700+ offices - Million Dollar Member of the LJ Hooker Captain''s Club – a select group designed to recognise and reward top performers.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Steven Khawam&nbsp;sales statistics</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>12 month period to&nbsp;October 23rd, 2019</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Steven Khawam from&nbsp;<a href="https://www.domain.com.au/real-estate-agencies/ljhookerguildford-27107/">LJ Hooker Guildford</a>&nbsp;has sold 25 properties in the last 12 months , with an average sale price of $697k and total sales valued at $16.7m*.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Steven sold 18 houses and 7 apartments with 15 sales by private treaty and 10 by auction, and these properties were on the market for an average of 52 days.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Steven''s highest recorded sale price was $1.6m for&nbsp;<a href="https://www.domain.com.au/45-kirkham-road-auburn-nsw-2144-2014905061">45 Kirkham Road, Auburn NSW 2144</a>, a 3-bedroom house which sold by auction on February 23rd, 2019, and was on the market for 29 days.</p>\r\n','','full_html'),('node','agent','0','41','41','und','0','<h2>About&nbsp;Matt Carpenter</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>A long-term local resident, Matthew Carpenter is easily recognised in the district and well known for his approachability and friendly nature. With a happy and infectious character, combined with an exceptionally professional and honest attitude, he has achieved incredible success in an illustrious Real Estate career.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>As Director at Starr Partners, Matthew has cultivated an impressive understanding of the many intricacies involved in achieving consistent and award winning success both personally and with his dedicated Real Estate team.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Starting his Real Estate career in 1997, Matthew has nurtured a well rounded and complete understanding of the industry having started out in Strata Management where he honed a deep empathy for client needs while developing fantastic communication skills. His friendly, hard-working attitude, combined with a commitment to always doing his best for every client, has seen Matthew regularly recognised as one of the leading sales agents in the Starr Partners Group. Having regularly achieved number one positions as Lister of the Year, Sales Creator of the Year and Salesperson for the Year, Matthew always strives to achieve better and serve as a shining example of honesty, integrity and tenacity to all that work with him.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Matthew''s many achievements and successes in local real estate prove his commitment to getting the best results for his clients at all times with a track record that speaks for itself. Supported by over 60 staff from Starr Partners Merrylands, Pemulwuy and Wentworthville offices, Matthew is focussed on fine tuning organisational processes and techniques to ensure his office maintains its top of class status while consistently delivering exceptional service, support and results to every customer.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Matt Carpenter&nbsp;sales statistics</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>12 month period to&nbsp;October 23rd, 2019</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Matt Carpenter from&nbsp;<a href="https://www.domain.com.au/real-estate-agencies/starrpartnersmerrylands-1966/">Starr Partners Merrylands</a>&nbsp;has sold 48 properties in the last 12 months , with an average sale price of $728k and total sales valued at $34.2m*. Matt worked with&nbsp;<a href="https://www.domain.com.au/real-estate-agent/jordan-laoulach-1566392/">Jordan Laoulach</a>,&nbsp;<a href="https://www.domain.com.au/real-estate-agent/milad-chaar-825401/">Milad Chaar</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href="https://www.domain.com.au/real-estate-agent/ramin-rahimi-1253889/">Ramin Rahimi</a>&nbsp;on 15 of these sales.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Matt sold 37 houses and 11 apartments with 38 sales by private treaty and 10 by auction, and these properties were on the market for an average of 88 days.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Matt''s highest recorded sale price was $1.7m for&nbsp;<a href="https://www.domain.com.au/2-valda-street-merrylands-nsw-2160-2014984452">2 Valda Street, Merrylands NSW 2160</a>, a 4-bedroom house which sold by auction on March 30th, 2019, and was on the market for 26 days.</p>\r\n','','full_html');
INSERT INTO `field_data_body` VALUES ('node','agent','0','42','42','und','0','<h2>About&nbsp;Joseph Nasr</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Joseph Nasr has a reputation for setting new sales records. His extraordinary negotiating skills and ability to produce standout marketing campaigns have seen him consistently set new benchmarks homes in the area.<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	His achievements have not gone unnoticed, with Joseph ranking within the top sales people in the entire LJ Hooker worldwide network of 700+ offices. Joseph is also a distinguished Multi-Million Dollar Member of the LJ Hooker Captain''s Club – a select group designed to recognise and reward top performers.<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	His reputation is such that he is often called to sell properties in other areas of Sydney, and he has a strong core of repeat and referral business with clients who have benefited from his services for many years.<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	With over 15 years of real estate experience behind him and a driving passion for this industry and the business itself, Joseph offers a level of service and a record of achievements that is unique in this area.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Joseph Nasr&nbsp;sales statistics</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>12 month period to&nbsp;October 23rd, 2019</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Joseph Nasr from&nbsp;<a href="https://www.domain.com.au/real-estate-agencies/ljhookerguildford-27107/">LJ Hooker Guildford</a>&nbsp;has sold 20 properties in the last 12 months , with an average sale price of $712k and total sales valued at $13.5m*.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Joseph sold 13 houses and 7 apartments with 9 sales by private treaty and 11 by auction, and these properties were on the market for an average of 38 days.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Joseph''s highest recorded sale price was $1.2m for&nbsp;<a href="https://www.domain.com.au/15-eleanor-street-rosehill-nsw-2142-2015349639">15 Eleanor Street, Rosehill NSW 2142</a>, a 7-bedroom house which sold prior to auction on June 28th, 2019, and was on the market for 16 days.</p>\r\n','','full_html'),('node','agent','0','43','43','und','0','<h2>About&nbsp;Greg Okladnikov</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>As a Director of Starr Partners Auburn, and long-term sales manager with close to 20 years experience with Real Estate sales in the local area, Greg has an unsurpassed knowledge of the movement and trends of the western suburbs property market. When combined with an in-depth understanding of the real-estate market in general, he brings enormous value to vendors and buyers in every engagement.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Greg is a licensed Real Estate agent with formal training as an educator. This background coupled with a high work-ethic, has seen him not only achieve outstanding results for his customers on a regular basis, but has him ranked in the Top 10 sales people in the Starr Partners Group for more than 10 years, achieve top auction listing agent for the last three years, while also developing and delivering quality training for other sales professionals.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Greg leads by example with a methodical and direct style coupled with high moral values and an honest attitude making him a great communicator. Committed to the continual refinement of systems and to helping those around him become the very best they can be, Greg is not only an expert in real estate sales, but a sought after mentor, instructor and teacher to other real estate professionals.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Greg Okladnikov&nbsp;sales statistics</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>12 month period to&nbsp;October 23rd, 2019</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Greg Okladnikov from&nbsp;<a href="https://www.domain.com.au/real-estate-agencies/starrpartnersauburn-22103/">Starr Partners Auburn</a>&nbsp;has sold 39 properties in the last 12 months , with an average sale price of $743k and total sales valued at $28.2m*. Greg worked with&nbsp;<a href="https://www.domain.com.au/real-estate-agent/ali-zavari-1653427/">Ali Zavari</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href="https://www.domain.com.au/real-estate-agent/steve-sanders-1562881/">Steve Sanders</a>&nbsp;on 3 of these sales.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Greg sold 30 houses and 9 apartments with 27 sales by private treaty and 12 by auction, and these properties were on the market for an average of 79 days.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Greg''s highest recorded sale price was $1.4m for&nbsp;<a href="https://www.domain.com.au/23-angus-ave-auburn-nsw-2144-2014912607">23 Angus Ave, Auburn NSW 2144</a>, a 4-bedroom house which sold by auction on February 23rd, 2019, and was on the market for 24 days.</p>\r\n','','full_html');
INSERT INTO `field_data_body` VALUES ('node','agent','0','44','44','und','0','<h2>About&nbsp;Vinesh Goundar</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Vinesh began his real estate career in Auburn in 1998 after completing a Diploma in Business Studies.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>He brings a unique and highly valued opinion to the role of Sales Consultant at Starr Partners Auburn, having lived in the area for over 20 years. His extensive local market knowledge has been a valuable asset in developing and maintaining a range of valuable ties with businesses and associations within the local community.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>His personal approach to the job at hand and dedication to providing that extra care factor really impresses his clients and sets him apart from the rest, with a number of repeat clients continually seeking his services.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Vinesh believes that having empathy with his clients is a key quality that every agent should have, and helps him to provide a highly professional, friendly and straight forward service when it comes to buying and selling real estate.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Vinesh Goundar&nbsp;sales statistics</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>12 month period to&nbsp;October 23rd, 2019</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Vinesh Goundar from&nbsp;<a href="https://www.domain.com.au/real-estate-agencies/starrpartnersauburn-22103/">Starr Partners Auburn</a>&nbsp;has sold 17 properties in the last 12 months , with an average sale price of $648k and total sales valued at $11.0m*.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Vinesh sold 9 houses and 8 apartments by private treaty, and these properties were on the market for an average of 84 days.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Vinesh''s highest recorded sale price was $970k for&nbsp;<a href="https://www.domain.com.au/16-cardigan-street-auburn-nsw-2144-2014740580">16 Cardigan Street, Auburn NSW 2144</a>, a 4-bedroom house which sold by private treaty on April 18th, 2019, and was on the market for 171 days.</p>\r\n','','full_html'),('node','agent','0','45','45','und','0','<h2>About&nbsp;Alistair Agius</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Alistair Agius is on a