INSERT INTO `field_revision_body` VALUES ('node','agent','0','46','46','und','0','<h2>About&nbsp;Terri Godfrey</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Boasting a long and successful career in Real Estate supported by a solid background in the banking industry, Terri Godfrey has personally witnessed the many fluctuations in the Western Sydney property market over the years to give her a rare insight into residential real estate that few others can share.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Highly respected for her integrity, helpfulness and honesty, Terri has a strong reputation not only as an agent who consistently gets great results for her customers, but as someone who cares deeply about doing an exceptional and thorough job every time.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Having lived in and around the Merrylands area for most of her life, Terri has an impressive list of personal and business relationships with developers, buyers and vendors who are consistently impressed with her excellent service.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A passionate music lover who often breaks into song, Terri exudes a bubbly, fun and highly approachable personality. Warm and vivacious, yet deeply caring and considerate, Terri is not only a great listener, but an exceptional communicator.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Highly successful having achieved top 10 results within the Starr partners group on several occasions, Terri is fiercely competitive and highly committed to consistently high achievement. This competitive nature combined with a love of sport, local knowledge and friendly personality makes her one of the best known, and highly sought after real estate agents in the area.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Terri Godfrey&nbsp;sales statistics</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>12 month period to&nbsp;October 23rd, 2019</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Terri Godfrey from&nbsp;<a href="https://www.domain.com.au/real-estate-agencies/starrpartnersmerrylands-1966/">Starr Partners Merrylands</a>&nbsp;has sold 16 properties in the last 12 months , with an average sale price of $664k and total sales valued at $10.6m*. Terri worked with&nbsp;<a href="https://www.domain.com.au/real-estate-agent/vinuka-perera-1473184/">Vinuka Perera</a>,&nbsp;<a href="https://www.domain.com.au/real-estate-agent/jennifer-kehoe-1253899/">Jennifer Kehoe</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href="https://www.domain.com.au/real-estate-agent/daniel-starr-827329/">Daniel Starr</a>&nbsp;on 10 of these sales.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Terri sold 10 houses and 6 apartments with 13 sales by private treaty and 3 by auction, and these properties were on the market for an average of 54 days.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Terri''s highest recorded sale price was $1.2m for&nbsp;<a href="https://www.domain.com.au/62-belmont-street-merrylands-nsw-2160-2015002644">62 Belmont Street, Merrylands NSW 2160</a>, a 4-bedroom house which sold by auction on April 6th, 2019, and was on the market for 26 days.</p>\r\n','','full_html');
INSERT INTO `field_revision_body` VALUES ('node','agent','0','47','47','und','0','<h2>About&nbsp;Milad Chaar</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>As Associate Director and Licensee in charge of Starr Partners Wentworthville, Milad Chaar is dedicated to the development of his team to continue their positive reputation of providing the best local results through exceptional service and support.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Milad has been a member of the Starr Partners team since 2000 having accumulated a comprehensive knowledge of the local area which gives him and his team an obvious advantage when helping buyers and sellers to achieve exceptional results. A Licensed Real Estate Agent who also holds an Advanced Diploma in Real Estate Business Management, Milad’s envious list of achievements has seen him regularly ranked as one of the Top Sales Agents in the Starr Partners Group since 2004.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>An expert in major residential development, Milad has been intrinsically involved in several major local area constructions including the Wynyard Street Guildford Development Project, NHL Developments on the Memorial Street Merrylands Project and the Boomerang Street Pty Ltd Granville Project.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A husband and father of three children, Milad’s caring and bubbly personality has seen him assemble a wide array of social and professional contacts amongst a diverse range of local communities. A dedicated family man and loyal work colleague, Milad believes that good family morals and an honest approach to everything you do is the foundation to achieving life’s personal and career goals.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Milad Chaar&nbsp;sales statistics</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>12 month period to&nbsp;October 23rd, 2019</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Milad Chaar from&nbsp;<a href="https://www.domain.com.au/real-estate-agencies/starrpartnersmerrylands-1966/">Starr Partners Merrylands</a>&nbsp;has sold 24 properties in the last 12 months , with an average sale price of $691k and total sales valued at $16.6m*. Milad worked with&nbsp;<a href="https://www.domain.com.au/real-estate-agent/ilhan-olca-1545610/">Ilhan Olca</a>,&nbsp;<a href="https://www.domain.com.au/real-estate-agent/matt-carpenter-1494146/">Matt Carpenter</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href="https://www.domain.com.au/real-estate-agent/mark-hole-1253894/">Mark Hole</a>&nbsp;on 14 of these sales.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Milad sold 14 houses, 9 apartments and 1 block of land or rural property with 20 sales by private treaty and 4 by auction, and these properties were on the market for an average of 87 days.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Milad''s highest recorded sale price was $1.4m for&nbsp;<a href="https://www.domain.com.au/7-slapp-street-merrylands-nsw-2160-2014775987">7 Slapp Street, Merrylands NSW 2160</a>, a 5-bedroom house which sold by private treaty on January 23rd, 2019, and was on the market for 72 days.</p>\r\n','','full_html');
INSERT INTO `field_revision_body` VALUES ('node','custom_article','0','48','48','und','0','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Greyhound Hotel, St Kilda site is for sale again.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The sad saga of the site of St Kilda’s much-loved-but-lost Greyhound Hotel has entered a new phase with the search for its next owner.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ironically, “boutique hotel developers” have shown interest in the razed site where the iconic drag and LGBTIQ venue stood before a previous owner demolished it.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>CBRE has been appointed by failed developer Steller’s receiver and manager KordaMentha to run the sales campaign culminating in a mortgagee auction on November 22.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>RELATED:&nbsp;<a href="https://www.heraldsun.com.au/news/victoria/last-drinks-the-popular-melbourne-pubs-we-have-lost-and-a-few-that-are-under-threat/news-story/f4ef6c68e46cc4bfdf61d9a4d2bb8452" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">Last drinks: The popular Melbourne pubs we lost</a></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><a href="https://www.heraldsun.com.au/leader/inner-south/former-greyhound-hotel-site-in-st-kilda-up-for-sale/news-story/9fcd305db3248f2bfa192a3d785cd48b" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">Former Greyhound Hotel site in St Kilda up for sale</a></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><a href="https://www.realestate.com.au/news/rosebud-property-owned-by-steller-sells-for-235m-less/?rsf=syn:news:nca:hs:socref" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">Rosebud property owned by Steller sells for $2.35m less</a></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="Greyhound Hotel" height="720" src="https://www.realestate.com.au/blog/images/1280x720-fit,progressive/2019/10/22142556/capi_495ccd88141af8d5f001f45dc568a09e_0833dd160322f370690fdd410c9201c0.jpeg" width="1280" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Greyhound prior to demolition. Picture: Yuri Kouzmin</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="Greyhound Hotel" height="720" src="https://www.realestate.com.au/blog/images/1280x720-fit,progressive/2019/10/22142603/capi_495ccd88141af8d5f001f45dc568a09e_e41f0429b3ebc41d049571dda187cf33.jpeg" width="1280" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Many would have had great nights start and finish walking through those doors. Picture: Yuri Kouzmin</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Steller bought the 911sq m corner site at 1 Brighton Rd for $7.5 million in 2017 and had planned to develop the site, flattened by its owner before that, before it collapsed.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Three street frontages, permit approval for a seven-level building — including 34 apartments and three shops — and commercial-one zoning opposite St Kilda Town Hall are the attractions, with potential for a developer to secure it for less than it fetched in 2017.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>CBRE’s Mark Wizel told the&nbsp;<em>Herald Sun</em>&nbsp;there had been “strong interest” in the site from a range of developers and expected it to attract offers “in excess of $5 million”.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Some interested parties would “continue to progress” the vision outlined in the approved permits, while other interest had come from “boutique hotel developers, as well as some developers looking at a built-to-rent type product and commercial office builders”.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Step into the amazing Pumphouse converted hotel</p>\r\n\r\n<p><iframe src="https://imasdk.googleapis.com/js/core/bridge3.344.0_en.html#goog_1992388869"></iframe></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Play Video</p>\r\n\r\n<p>1:12</p>\r\n\r\n<p>“I think the buyer would definitely use the envelope for the seven-level building with apartments and shops on the ground floor … but they might change it from apartments to hotel rooms or from apartments to offices,” he said.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The 163-year-old pub was destroyed despite&nbsp;<a href="https://www.heraldsun.com.au/leader/inner-south/melbournes-iconic-greyhound-hotel-gay-bar-closes-for-good/news-story/179317f7f55b2f576eb58d21177963cb" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">campaigns to save it,&nbsp;</a>including a&nbsp;<a href="https://www.heraldsun.com.au/leader/inner-south/greyhound-hotel-faces-demolition-as-planning-minister-richard-wynne-refuses-interim-heritage-controls/news-story/af3e5d430244b89c05fb9dc67dd8a7ed" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">bid for heritage protection</a>&nbsp;that&nbsp;<a href="https://www.heraldsun.com.au/leader/inner-south/former-greyhound-hotel-site-in-st-kilda-up-for-sale/news-story/9fcd305db3248f2bfa192a3d785cd48b" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">failed to persuade Planning Minister Richard Wynne</a>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Greyhound regular&nbsp;<a href="https://www.heraldsun.com.au/leader/inner-south/greyhound-hotel-patrons-scavenge-for-bricks-plaster-memorabilia-at-demolition-site/news-story/17262122a1a0e91fcfb5a1f3a9c5c91d" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">Julie Marrington told Port Phillip Leader in 2017</a>&nbsp;she made four trips to the site to scavenge for bricks to share among its locals following its demolition.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>“It meant so many things to so many different people for all sorts of reasons — for many it was our lounge room,” she said.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>“Everybody was exceptionally sad when it was torn down.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>“That’s more than 160 years worth of history just gone.”</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="Greyhound gone" height="720" src="https://www.realestate.com.au/blog/images/1280x720-fit,progressive/2019/10/22142608/capi_495ccd88141af8d5f001f45dc568a09e_6ef9a60d68a0650a9d0de6b306d1dc7b.jpeg" width="1280" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Julie Marrington with a brick from the demolition of the Greyhound Hotel. Picture: Hamish Blair</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" height="720" src="https://www.realestate.com.au/blog/images/1280x720-fit,progressive/2019/10/22142613/capi_495ccd88141af8d5f001f45dc568a09e_28cd1440a84dbb916ec3327afffd3498.jpeg" width="1280" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>An artist’s impression of a proposed eight-storey apartment complex on the site.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Art Deco-style facade of the building was constructed over the original in the late 1930s, which later&nbsp;<a href="https://www.heraldsun.com.au/news/victoria/last-drinks-the-popular-melbourne-pubs-we-have-lost-and-a-few-that-are-under-threat/news-story/f4ef6c68e46cc4bfdf61d9a4d2bb8452" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">disqualified the venue from heritage listing</a>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Rebranded as GH in its later years, the hotel was home to drag shows and drag bingo; it was also a nightclub.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Sorrento’s iconic Continental Hotel is also in limbo after Steller’s collapse, while a Rosebud property owned by the failed developer&nbsp;<a href="https://www.realestate.com.au/news/rosebud-property-owned-by-steller-sells-for-235m-less/?rsf=syn:news:nca:hs:socref" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">sold for $2.35 million less than it was bought for</a>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Mark Wizel shares the former Greyhound Hotel site listing with other CBRE Victorian development site sales team members Julian White, David Minty and Chao Zhang.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>“The site’s permit will be a key selling point as will the flexible zoning, which allows for a variety of end uses,” Mr White said.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>“The location will be another drawcard, with the property situated in walking distance of major retail hubs and public transport.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>MORE:&nbsp;<a href="https://www.realestate.com.au/news/enoteca-sileno-original-home-of-carlton-north-icon-sold/?rsf=syn:news:nca:hs:socref" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">Enoteca Sileno: original home of Carlton North icon sold</a></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><a href="https://www.realestate.com.au/news/darren-thornburgh-home-denise-foster-lists-house-they-shared/?rsf=syn:news:nca:hs:socref" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">Darren Thornburgh home: Denise Foster lists house they shared</a></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><a href="https://www.realestate.com.au/news/melbourne-house-price-records-by-council-region-revealed/?rsf=syn:news:nca:hs:socref" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">Melbourne house price records by council region revealed</a></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><a href="mailto:scott.carbines@news.com.au" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">scott.carbines@news.com.au</a></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href="https://www.realestate.com.au/news/vic/melbourne/" title="View all posts in Melbourne">MELBOURNE&nbsp;</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href="https://www.realestate.com.au/news/" title="View all posts in news">NEWS&nbsp;</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href="https://www.realestate.com.au/news/vic/" title="View all posts in Victoria">VICTORIA</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n','','full_html');
INSERT INTO `field_revision_body` VALUES ('node','custom_article','0','49','49','und','0','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>94 St Vincent St, Port Adelaide may just be Australia’s edgiest townhouse.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Edgy, unique, and colourful are among the plethora of adjectives one could use to describe this refurbished Port Adelaide townhouse.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Offered to the market via an expression of interest campaign, the two-home property at 94 St Vincent St, was purchased by the vendors in 2013, who were drawn to the area by its rich history and industrial texture.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>At the time, the 1900’s building resembled not much more than a shopfront and was originally built as a photographic studio for A.E Bond, based on St Vincent St, in the bustling seaside hub.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>MORE NEWS:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href="https://www.realestate.com.au/news/legendary-sports-commentator-bruce-mcavaney-lists-adelaide-beachside-home/?rsf=syn:news:nca:aa:spa">Legendary sports commentator Bruce McAvaney lists Adelaide beachside home</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href="https://www.realestate.com.au/news/waterfront-home-sets-new-residential-sales-record-for-semaphore-south/?rsf=syn:news:nca:aa:spa">Waterfront home sets new residential sales record for Semaphore South</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href="https://www.realestate.com.au/news/hot-property-the-sa-suburbs-leading-the-nation/?rsf=syn:news:nca:aa:spa">Hot property: The SA suburbs leading the nation</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The ultimate home for cat lovers</p>\r\n\r\n<p><iframe src="https://imasdk.googleapis.com/js/core/bridge3.344.0_en.html#goog_1251631546"></iframe></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Play Video</p>\r\n\r\n<p>1:06</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" height="1024" src="https://www.realestate.com.au/blog/images/768x1024-fit,progressive/2019/10/22030015/capi_d8f9a34ad7a79ed2040530f311647c18_171b6dde6ad6c1af6873674bcdc46caa.jpeg" width="768" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>94 St Vincent St, Port Adelaide</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" height="720" src="https://www.realestate.com.au/blog/images/1280x720-fit,progressive/2019/10/22030023/capi_d8f9a34ad7a79ed2040530f311647c18_4de030dfd21f64d3fd38f6ccd36677bd.jpeg" width="1280" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>94 St Vincent St, Port Adelaide</p>\r\n\r\n<p>“As you follow the Baltic flooring towards the rear of the building, you locate the original dark room, now encompassing the courtyard where the old wall remains,” the vendor said.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>“That’s followed by the studio, where the photographer captured rites of passage and local history, birthdays, weddings, soldiers and sailors departing for war.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>“It was here in the studio where some 1,500 glass negatives were discovered and are now housed at the maritime museum.”</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The new owner’s idea was to incorporate a studio and home on a narrow footprint drawing in light from all directions.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The result was Bond Studio – a totally self-contained home within the original building – and the impressive Bond House – three bedrooms and four bathrooms over three levels – at the rear.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" height="720" src="https://www.realestate.com.au/blog/images/1280x720-fit,progressive/2019/10/22030029/capi_d8f9a34ad7a79ed2040530f311647c18_68c9c295094f23edcd8c7509f6ff59c8.jpeg" width="1280" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>94 St Vincent St, Port Adelaide</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" height="720" src="https://www.realestate.com.au/blog/images/1280x720-fit,progressive/2019/10/22030033/capi_d8f9a34ad7a79ed2040530f311647c18_7cde56c6b73d72dd26d2ee85f022bd4d.jpeg" width="1280" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>94 St Vincent St, Port Adelaide</p>\r\n\r\n<p>“Dealing with the heritage protection was eased by the generous support of the local Port Adelaide Council,” the vendor said.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>“This allowed the modest street aspect of the studio to stay – as the three-storey extension is behind St Vincent Street – bringing at its peak 360-degree views of the entire city.”</p>\r\n\r\n<p>An incredible artwork on display within the home embraces another layer of Port Adelaide’s rich history.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>“The exterior, three-storey work was created by Venice-based artist Peeta, as part of Wonderwalls Port Adelaide and The Big Picture Fest 2019,” the vendor said.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>“The interior mural found in the courtyard is by Adelaide based artist Joel van Moore (Vans the Omega).”</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" height="720" src="https://www.realestate.com.au/blog/images/1280x720-fit,progressive/2019/10/22030038/capi_d8f9a34ad7a79ed2040530f311647c18_b2fa0e77f6a45a137699b8d3cab9536a.jpeg" width="1280" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>94 St Vincent St, Port Adelaide</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" height="720" src="https://www.realestate.com.au/blog/images/1280x720-fit,progressive/2019/10/22030043/capi_d8f9a34ad7a79ed2040530f311647c18_2661c24e0eef24788667762a2d1a7162.jpeg" width="1280" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>94 St Vincent St, Port Adelaide</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ray White Port Adelaide Director Nick Psarros said he was enthralled by the property.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>“I have a lot of fabulous properties, but this one is so different. You have history and you have a studio,” he said.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>“You also have this amazing art and put simply, this property is just very exciting. It’s a blend of architecture and art.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>“You can run your business from the front property and live in the brand-new home or lease out the front property and derive an income.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>“There are so many choices and it’s in such a great location. You can Immerse yourself in the heart of Port Adelaide with everything at your fingertips.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>“The Port is fast becoming a suburb of choice and now with the brand-new Port Adelaide Plaza in full swing with restaurants, cafes, Aldi and retail, the area is buzzing.”</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" height="720" src="https://www.realestate.com.au/blog/images/1280x720-fit,progressive/2019/10/22030224/capi_d8f9a34ad7a79ed2040530f311647c18_1fedfb1a797ec9cc561abfc97e1629f7.jpeg" width="1280" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>94 St Vincent St, Port Adelaide</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" height="720" src="https://www.realestate.com.au/blog/images/1280x720-fit,progressive/2019/10/22030232/capi_d8f9a34ad7a79ed2040530f311647c18_913c3a461ddbb6d0b98da7f55392fee6.jpeg" width="1280" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>94 St Vincent St, Port Adelaide</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ultra cool orphanage conversion in Bendigo</p>\r\n\r\n<p>0:38</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href="https://www.realestate.com.au/news/sa/adelaide/" title="View all posts in Adelaide">ADELAIDE&nbsp;</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href="https://www.realestate.com.au/news/" title="View all posts in news">NEWS&nbsp;</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href="https://www.realestate.com.au/news/sa/" title="View all posts in South Australia">SOUTH AUSTRALIA</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n','','full_html');
INSERT INTO `field_revision_body` VALUES ('node','custom_article','0','50','50','und','0','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>18 Gower St, Glenelg East, was listed with Harris Real Estate.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A Glenelg East property proved buyers are all about location, attracting multiple offers and the state’s top sale record for last week.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The contemporary residence, at&nbsp;<a href="https://www.realestate.com.au/sold/property-house-sa-glenelg+east-132145318" title="www.realestate.com.au">18 Gower St</a>, attracted strong buyer interest and sold for $1.435 million – almost double Glenelg East’s median house price of $730,000, according to CoreLogic.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>MORE NEWS:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href="https://www.realestate.com.au/news/adelaides-blooming-market-has-agents-calling-for-more-properties/?rsf=syn:news:nca:aa:spa" title="www.realestate.com.au">Adelaide’s property market springs to life</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href="https://www.realestate.com.au/news/look-inside-australias-most-popular-auction-listing/?rsf=syn:news:nca:aa:spa" title="www.realestate.com.au">Inside Australia’s hottest auction listing</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href="https://www.realestate.com.au/news/revealed-adelaides-best-coastal-suburbs-for-property-buyers/?rsf=syn:news:nca:aa:spa" title="www.realestate.com.au">Central suburbs win Adelaide coastal victory</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" height="720" src="https://www.realestate.com.au/blog/images/1280x720-fit,progressive/2019/10/22010014/capi_ab5c308fd595f68e49c265db5f3dda12_d6cddfb02e4624bc6062248944c02a15.jpeg" width="1280" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>18 Gower St, Glenelg East</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" height="720" src="https://www.realestate.com.au/blog/images/1280x720-fit,progressive/2019/10/22010021/capi_ab5c308fd595f68e49c265db5f3dda12_294cb46264d6b026937e774d6f249f0a.jpeg" width="1280" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>18 Gower St, Glenelg East</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Harris Real Estate selling agent Karen Dorman said she expected a strong result, especially given the quality on offer.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>“We had a guide of $1.358 million to $1.45 million and thought where it sat was good,” she said.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>“We had two open inspections which attracted 49 groups and it sold half an hour before the third open.”</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Attracting a variety of buyers, Ms Dorman said the four-bedroom home was particularly popular with families looking to break into the suburb.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" height="720" src="https://www.realestate.com.au/blog/images/1280x720-fit,progressive/2019/10/22010025/capi_ab5c308fd595f68e49c265db5f3dda12_015edf1115a1ae75ba8db54b8b0f38a4.jpeg" width="1280" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>18 Gower St, Glenelg East</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>6 Australian wow homes that have just sold</p>\r\n\r\n<p><iframe src="https://imasdk.googleapis.com/js/core/bridge3.344.0_en.html#goog_858259954"></iframe></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Play Video</p>\r\n\r\n<p>1:20</p>\r\n\r\n<p>“We had a lot of families and a lot of people heading towards a less-maintenance property that live locally – it’s arguably one of the best streets in Glenelg East,” she said.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>“The location is sensational and highly sought-after, especially to get a newer dwelling. Not everyone wants a character property, so when something like this comes up it is very sought-after.”</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Built by TEK Building &amp; Design, the bespoke home featured a luxurious master suite, a study, two bedrooms, a family bathroom, an open-plan kitchen, a living and dining area, a larder, a laundry and a private lounge or optional bedroom.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The home also had a generous alfresco, complete with an outdoor kitchen and neat, landscaped backyard.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" height="720" src="https://www.realestate.com.au/blog/images/1280x720-fit,progressive/2019/10/22010032/capi_ab5c308fd595f68e49c265db5f3dda12_5c4a74a6853b19ef8eab2ea9f00f88d8.jpeg" width="1280" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>18 Gower St, Glenelg East</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" height="720" src="https://www.realestate.com.au/blog/images/1280x720-fit,progressive/2019/10/22010037/capi_ab5c308fd595f68e49c265db5f3dda12_c97e4bc0f283b2bc3dab28e5555960ae.jpeg" width="1280" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>18 Gower St, Glenelg East</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ms Dorman said buyers loved the floorplan and the high-quality features on offer, with a keen attention to detail throughout the home.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>“The frontage has a real Hamptons vibe, the feedback was really positive,” she said.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>“Buyers really liked the home office, the separate theatre space, the open-plan living and the ability to drive another car through and have three cars undercover – that was a real stand out.”</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href="https://www.realestate.com.au/news/sa/adelaide/" title="View all posts in Adelaide">ADELAIDE&nbsp;</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href="https://www.realestate.com.au/news/" title="View all posts in news">NEWS&nbsp;</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href="https://www.realestate.com.au/news/sa/" title="View all posts in South Australia">SOUTH AUSTRALIA</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n','','full_html');
INSERT INTO `field_revision_body` VALUES ('node','product','0','51','51','und','0','<p>We are delighted to invite you to view this sublime Luxury Residence. Please contact Stephanie Williams 0413 874 888 or John Williams 0411 747 555 to register for our inspections of this stunning home this Saturday 26th of October 2019. Please note that registration prior to inspection is essential.<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	"Undoubtedly one of South Australia''s most outstanding prestige properties that truly presents an exclusive once in a lifetime opportunity. Extensively renovated and extended by Gray Constructions with absolute precision and attention to detail. The home eclipses all previous standards of luxury family living and features a dazzling renovation &amp; stunning contemporary extension, resort-style swimming pool, established designer gardens and three-car side by side garaging accessed via Winchester Lane with a separate studio/home office located above that is privately accessed from Hewitt Avenue.This luxury family residence exudes sophistication and elegance like no other. Nestled among other prestige homes in one of exclusive Rose Park''s premier tree-lined streets. Commanding special appeal and out of this world luxury," John &amp; Stephanie Williams - WILLIAMS LUXURY<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	Proudly positioned on beautiful Prescott Terrace, you are unlikely to find a home quite so flawless, so sun-lit and so architecturally captivating as this sublime Bay Window Bluestone Villa C.1900. The exciting improvements and impressive extensions carried out over C.2011/C.2014 and C.2017 harmoniously combine the character features with vogue contemporary style and ensure the very best in luxury lifestyle living. The home is sited on a valuable corner allotment of some 1579sqm approx. in exclusive and tightly held Rose Park. A place of breathtaking luxury and contemporary style, where busy family life and opportunities to entertain can play out in perfect synchronicity, enhanced by gorgeous luxe high-end selections, stunning designer landscaped gardens, statement lighting and complimented by beautiful natural light that cascades throughout.<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	The residence offers a spectacular blueprint of 648sqm approx. of sophisticated living &amp; entertaining. Comprising magnificent formal &amp; family living spaces, four bedrooms, including a spectacular master bedroom suite with a fashionista''s dressing room and luxe ensuite bathroom, wrap around verandah, gorgeous designer gardens, family bathroom with designer bathtub, luxe powder room and presidential style library/formal lounge with built in bookcases and stunning French antique chandelier. Follow the divine timber floorboards to the stunning new main living &amp; entertaining spaces, chef-inspired kitchen with central island bench, Siemens induction cooktop and twin integrated dishwashers, Neff double wall ovens, warming drawer, integrated Electrolux fridge &amp; freezer and walk in pantry, sumptuous living/dining area with a gas fireplace where you can enjoy fine dining or fun dinner parties. There is also a children''s play room/teenagers retreat with sliding doors opening out to the terrace, the ultimate family laundry room with endless storage and a stunning lower ground floor level featuring a study/home theatre room and irresistible wine collector''s cellar.<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	Enjoy entertaining family and friends with superb versatility and the perfect seamless infusion of indoor/outdoor living with the stunning entertainers pavilion that leads out to the gorgeous Virginia Kennett designer gardens and solar heated swimming pool. A car lover''s dream with garaging for three side by side cars accessed via Winchester Lane and also featuring a spacious detached studio/home office/teenagers retreat complete with kitchenette &amp; bathroom which is perfect for the creative buyer to work from home. This space also offers incredible Velux skylights and direct access to Hewitt Avenue with a separate intercom system.<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	This amazing residence offers unsurpassed luxury that is sure to seduce the luxury family buyer who commands the very best of everything in life…<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	Please note the property is on two titles - CT 5774/762 on 884sqm approx and CT 5731/562 on 695sqm approx. Total 1579sqm approx<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	French tessellated tiled verandah<br />\r\n	Bronze Victorian fountain in front garden<br />\r\n	International statement lighting<br />\r\n	Spotted Gum timber floors<br />\r\n	Lush wool carpets<br />\r\n	Plantation shutters<br />\r\n	Character fireplaces<br />\r\n	Underfloor radiant heating in bathrooms<br />\r\n	Designer wallpaper<br />\r\n	Velux skylights<br />\r\n	Feature light sculpture over the dining room table - specially commissioned from the Jam Factory.<br />\r\n	Steel double-glazed windows in the open plan area - made in Melbourne<br />\r\n	Ceiling lantern in living area with operable windows via remote<br />\r\n	French antique 18th century limestone mantelpiece<br />\r\n	Gas "real flame" fire<br />\r\n	Siemens freezone induction cooktop and fully integrated dishwashers (x2)<br />\r\n	Neff double wall oven and large size warming drawer<br />\r\n	Integrated fridge and freezer<br />\r\n	Qasair concealed range hood<br />\r\n	Wine collectors cellar with lockable door and custom shelving<br />\r\n	Fully automated watering system<br />\r\n	Bocce court<br />\r\n	Raised vegetable garden beds<br />\r\n	Solar heated swimming pool with Hydroxypure chlorination system<br />\r\n	Generous 3 car garaging with separate garden shed and storage for bikes<br />\r\n	Split system R/C air conditioning in upstairs studio<br />\r\n	Intercom system to all gates<br />\r\n	Monitored back to base security alarm<br />\r\n	Reverse cycle air conditioning to all rooms including bathrooms<br />\r\n	Water softener/filtration to entire house<br />\r\n	Solar hot water system<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	Rose Park is undoubtedly one of South Australia''s most popular suburbs within close proximity to vibrant, The Parade Norwood and it''s cafes, restaurants and shops, close to Dulwich Village, Burnside Village and a selection of popular schools including; Loreto College, Pembroke College, St Ignatius, Prince Alfred College and St Peter''s Girls.<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	CT Reference: 5731/562 &amp; 5774/762<br />\r\n	Year Built: C.1900<br />\r\n	Living: 648sqm (approx.)<br />\r\n	Land: 1,579sqm (approx.)<br />\r\n	Council: City of Burnside<br />\r\n	Council Rates: $5,078.25 pa approx<br />\r\n	ESL: $426.20pa approx.<br />\r\n	SA Water: $613.15pq approx</p>\r\n','','full_html');
INSERT INTO `field_revision_body` VALUES ('node','product','0','52','52','und','0','<p>Expression of Interest | Closing Thursday 7th November at 5.00pm (Unless Sold Prior)<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	One of Northern Victoria’s most iconic properties forever associated with the emergence of the states winemaking industry in its heyday and the largest winery in the Southern Hemisphere established by G.F. Morris, completely restored in the 1970’s by Morris’s great granddaughter Melba Slamen-Morris, this 851.5 hectares approx. multi use property comprises the 1889 Italianate Mansion “Fairfield”, together with its remarkably preserved above ground massive double brick cellars, ferment house, Bond house, steam engines originally driven from central boiler and furnace, shearing shed, blacksmiths shops and stables, Separate cottages situated on Mount Ochtertyre Road and Popes Road/Gooramadda Road.<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	‘Fairfield’, Commissioned by G.F. Morris (to replace the original 1860’s home which had burnt out) and designed by local architects Gordon &amp; Gordon, the Italianate style mansion was built in 1889 using bricks quarried from the land behind the house which became a dam. Set approx. 260 meters back from the Murray Valley Highway it is a most imposing building with its lacework verandah and balcony above, orientated North South. Entrance is via the Eastern façade to an arched foyer that forms a gallery through the East West axis to a western doorway to the afternoon side of the verandah thus providing natural light all day. Off this gallery are the morning room, the central drawing room with bay windows and spectacular marble fireplace, the smoking room and opposite the billiard room. To the right of the entrance is the magnificent dining room with red marble fireplace. The huge ballroom, added in approx. 1897 for a governor’s state visit, fills in the east (maid’s rooms, bathroom and office) and west wing (kitchen with original ‘lux’ cast iron stove and separate scullery with original bakers’ oven, all with pine benches and built in original cupboards, and pantry/maids meals area next door. A fine staircase leads from the entrance foyer to a landing accessing the bedrooms of which there are a nursery (South-West facing), master bedroom (North-West facing), large guest bedroom over drawing room, SE corner bedroom, NE corner bedroom over the dining room. An upstairs bathroom and washroom lead to a secondary staircase down to the ballroom and service areas. External to the scullery is a storage shed and outside W.C. The surrounding cast-iron lacework enveloped balcony at the front of the home affords magnificent views over the property and surrounding countryside.<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=0r3BDNVo5u0<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	Should you require any further information, please contact Warwick Anderson on 0418 320 873 to receive full information memorandum.<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	Agents in Conjunction | Landmark Harcourts Albury | Billy Jones 0438 454 950</p>\r\n','','full_html');
